# os/engineering contract version — the forcing function against silent propagation lag

A single monotonic integer naming the current state of the engineering contract (CONTOUR.md +
VALIDATION.md + PROJECT_SETUP.md + profiles/**). A **MAINTENANCE session bumps it** (current + one
log line) whenever it hardens or adds a load-bearing gate (os/MAINTENANCE.md step 6). Each product
repo records the version it last synced to (`validation.config: synced_contract_version`); PROJECT_SETUP
stamps it at setup, §Re-sync updates it. `collect` / `audit` / `digest` compare the two and flag a repo
that is BEHIND, so an os/engineering hardening can no longer silently fail to reach the repo where work
runs (the root cause behind FRICTION 79/84/88/90/92 — propagation lag with no forcing function).

